01:14:51.220 --> 01:14:54.420
I am not a wuss!

01:14:54.725 --> 01:14:56.492
Wuss, wuss, wuss, wuss, wuss!

01:14:56.592 --> 01:15:00.246
- Oh, God, I hate you.
- I hate you!

01:15:02.348 --> 01:15:05.840
- Gimme that gun.
- It's all right. It's a Baretta .34...

01:15:09.555 --> 01:15:11.284
You're fired.

01:15:24.904 --> 01:15:26.964
Is he dead?

01:15:31.147 --> 01:15:33.147
Oh, great.

01:15:34.065 --> 01:15:38.145
Terrific. He decides to keep
the zoo open, so you kill him.

01:15:39.422 --> 01:15:41.002
Brilliant. Well done.

01:15:41.102 --> 01:15:44.773
Thank you so much, especially for
shooting him right between the eyes...

01:15:44.873 --> 01:15:47.443
so that it doesn't
look like an accident...

01:15:47.543 --> 01:15:50.748
because the people at Octopus will know
he was coming here to close us down.

01:15:50.848 --> 01:15:53.848
So there's our motive
for murdering him. Stunning.

01:15:53.948 --> 01:15:57.255
Well, Mr. Brain of Britain,
what are we going to tell the police...

01:15:57.355 --> 01:15:59.956
who are, of course,
already on their way here?

01:16:00.056 --> 01:16:04.194
Another example
of the thoroughness of your plan.

01:16:04.294 --> 01:16:05.942
Go on. I'm all ears.

01:16:08.118 --> 01:16:10.164
What do you suggest we do
with the dead body...

01:16:10.264 --> 01:16:12.233
of the incredibly famous man...

01:16:12.333 --> 01:16:15.383
who you have just assassinated?

01:16:17.529 --> 01:16:20.346
Sorry, I didn't quite catch it.
What?

01:16:20.446 --> 01:16:23.492
What was it?
Pop him in the blender?

01:16:25.270 --> 01:16:29.156
I know he's dead!
I did notice!

01:16:29.256 --> 01:16:31.004
Well... What?

01:16:41.855 --> 01:16:43.604
Give it, give it, give it...

01:16:43.704 --> 01:16:45.818
before you shoot somebody else!

01:16:50.965 --> 01:16:52.523
What are you doing?

01:16:53.300 --> 01:16:55.481
- I'm freezing him.
- Why?

01:16:55.581 --> 01:16:58.488
He's gotta be cryogenically
frozen until they find a cure!

01:16:58.588 --> 01:17:00.553
- A cure?
- Yeah.

01:17:00.653 --> 01:17:03.493
- He has a bullet in the brain.
- Well, get more ice!

01:17:03.593 --> 01:17:07.498
Vince, there is no cure
for a bullet in the brain.

01:17:07.598 --> 01:17:10.746
It is very fatal.

01:17:15.525 --> 01:17:18.756
- You mean he's dead?
- Yes.

01:17:20.229 --> 01:17:24.564
- And he's not coming back?
- No. I'm sorry.

01:17:33.776 --> 01:17:37.461
I'm so happy!
You're dead!

01:17:37.561 --> 01:17:40.933
You're dead!
You're dead!

01:17:41.033 --> 01:17:44.967
You big, fat bastard!

01:17:45.067 --> 01:17:46.989
Yes, Bugsy!

01:17:48.525 --> 01:17:50.459
High five! Low five!
I love ya!

01:17:51.895 --> 01:17:53.920
Life begins!

01:17:57.268 --> 01:17:59.517
So what are we gonna do?

01:17:59.617 --> 01:18:01.585
I never have to listen
to you again, do I?

01:18:01.685 --> 01:18:05.059
With your, "You're no son of mine,
you miserable little worm.

01:18:05.159 --> 01:18:09.125
You've been a disappointment
to me since the day...

01:18:09.225 --> 01:18:11.965
your mother
farted you out of her womb."

01:18:12.065 --> 01:18:13.299
Good idea!

01:18:13.399 --> 01:18:15.771
I need something to glue
the mustache down with.

01:18:15.871 --> 01:18:18.119
I need things for the hair.

01:18:20.327 --> 01:18:22.779
- Neville, that's good, mate.
- That's terrible.

01:18:22.879 --> 01:18:25.111
Oh, no, those eyebrows are terrible.

01:18:25.211 --> 01:18:27.150
- Squint your eyes together.
- Like that?

01:18:27.250 --> 01:18:29.314
- Right like that. Hold that.
- Careful!

01:18:29.414 --> 01:18:31.703
- Glasses!
- Oh, yeah, get the glasses.

01:18:34.143 --> 01:18:36.337
- Give me cotton balls.
- Hello, Inspector.

01:18:37.513 --> 01:18:39.571
Let's compare them.
Come on.

01:18:40.815 --> 01:18:42.997
Mr. McCain looks paler... much.

01:18:43.097 --> 01:18:45.035
- What do you think?
- He's dead, you idiot.

01:18:45.135 --> 01:18:49.541
- Oh, my God, it's not going to work.
- Oh, yes, it will.

01:18:49.641 --> 01:18:53.673
- No, no, no. We shall all go to jail.
- It's gonna go like clockwork.

01:18:53.773 --> 01:18:58.115
Hello, Neville.
Hello, Inspector.

01:18:58.215 --> 01:19:00.985
- That's very good!
- Do you have the will?

01:19:01.085 --> 01:19:04.119
- Very good indeed.
- It's very short.

01:19:04.219 --> 01:19:06.320
Yeah. The simpler it is,
the more watertight.

01:19:06.420 --> 01:19:08.827
So we're going to set the zoo up
as a trust... that's for all of us...

01:19:08.927 --> 01:19:12.095
and everything else goes to
"my son Vincent McCain, absolutely."

01:19:12.195 --> 01:19:15.709
- You mean, we get the zoo?
- Yeah.

01:19:18.457 --> 01:19:20.841
Let's get this body
up to my office. Let's go!

01:19:20.941 --> 01:19:24.041
- I don't think this is fair.
- Fair?

01:19:24.141 --> 01:19:26.546
- You get to run the zoo with Willa.
- Yes.

01:19:26.646 --> 01:19:29.515
Well, I think I love her.

01:19:29.615 --> 01:19:32.092
- What?
- I love Willa.

01:19:34.239 --> 01:19:35.717
No, I love her.

01:19:35.817 --> 01:19:38.258
No, I love her.

01:19:38.358 --> 01:19:40.857
- I love her.
- I love Willa!

01:19:40.957 --> 01:19:45.042
Look, I get Willa,
you get seven billion dollars.

01:19:47.919 --> 01:19:51.184
- Right. Right, okay.
- There's the gun.

01:19:52.391 --> 01:19:53.571
Here we go.

01:19:53.671 --> 01:19:56.374
Come along, come along.
We haven't got much time.

01:19:56.474 --> 01:20:00.045
- I'm worried about fooling Neville.
- Neville's gonna be tough.

01:20:00.145 --> 01:20:02.519
- Oh, my God!
- Hello, Willa.

01:20:02.619 --> 01:20:05.555
Hello, Neville! Hello!

01:20:05.655 --> 01:20:10.893
Hello, Neville. Excuse me, I'm going
to go have a pee. I'll be right there.

01:20:10.993 --> 01:20:14.162
- Right, boss.
- Hi! Great to see you.

01:20:14.262 --> 01:20:16.397
Hello. Willa Weston.

01:20:16.497 --> 01:20:19.133
Chief Superintendent Masefield,
Sgt. Scott and Sgt. Irving.

01:20:19.233 --> 01:20:22.121
- Rod will be with you in a moment.
- I'll be a moment.

01:20:24.193 --> 01:20:28.545
Power!
Gets 'em every time.

01:20:28.645 --> 01:20:31.122
Oh, yeah. That's better.

01:20:35.603 --> 01:20:37.988
Thank you, my dear.

01:20:38.088 --> 01:20:41.323
Hello, Neville.
Hello, Inspector.

01:20:41.423 --> 01:20:44.560
I'd like to introduce you
to Inspector Masefield.

01:20:44.660 --> 01:20:46.795
G'day. Good on ya.

01:20:46.895 --> 01:20:49.466
- Good outfit.
- It's an honour to meet you, Mr. McCain.

01:20:49.566 --> 01:20:52.905
Well, goody.
Hello, Neville.

01:20:53.005 --> 01:20:55.822
- Hello, Rod.
- Hello, Nev.

01:20:58.830 --> 01:21:02.080
- Have you spoken to Vince?
- Yes, I have.

01:21:02.180 --> 01:21:05.018
- Shall we arrest him now, sir?
- No, that won't be necessary.

01:21:05.118 --> 01:21:08.285
Vince and I have had a long talk.

01:21:08.385 --> 01:21:11.759
Between ourselves,
it was quite emotional.

01:21:11.859 --> 01:21:14.025
You haven't killed him,
have you, Rod?

01:21:14.125 --> 01:21:16.047
Nobody's killed anybody!

01:21:18.684 --> 01:21:21.698
Moron! No, I mean...

01:21:21.798 --> 01:21:23.603
that we've had a reconciliation.

01:21:23.703 --> 01:21:26.338
- Isn't it wonderful?
- A reconciliation?

01:21:26.438 --> 01:21:28.937
That's right, Neville.
Back, Neville.

01:21:29.037 --> 01:21:33.914
- So you're not pressing charges?
- On the contrary, Inspector.

01:21:34.014 --> 01:21:36.082
Not at all.
But I would like your assistance.

01:21:36.182 --> 01:21:38.819
I've just made out a new will
and I'd like you to witness it.

01:21:38.919 --> 01:21:41.188
- A new will?
- Bend down, Neville.

01:21:41.288 --> 01:21:43.557
- It would be a privilege, Mr. McCain.
- Thank you.

01:21:43.657 --> 01:21:45.895
What do you mean, a new will?

01:21:45.995 --> 01:21:49.866
As a result of my talk with Vince,
I've decided to leave Octopus to him.

01:21:49.966 --> 01:21:52.402
- What?
- Hold still!

01:21:52.502 --> 01:21:55.738
- Leave Octopus to Vince?
- Shut up! He's a good boy.

01:21:55.838 --> 01:21:58.742
