He's a total wanker, Rod!

01:21:58.842 --> 01:22:00.761
I won't have you
talk about him like that!

01:22:02.931 --> 01:22:05.315
Rod, he steals from you.

01:22:05.415 --> 01:22:08.583
That's only to get the attention I
should've given him when he was a child!

01:22:08.683 --> 01:22:11.555
But you can't leave Octopus
to that asshole!

01:22:11.655 --> 01:22:15.202
That asshole is my son!

01:22:17.580 --> 01:22:19.092
I love him.

01:22:19.192 --> 01:22:22.162
But you're always saying
what a complete wuss he is.

01:22:22.262 --> 01:22:23.616
I am not...

01:22:24.655 --> 01:22:28.751
going to let you
talk about him in that way.

01:22:45.564 --> 01:22:47.780
- Are you all right, mate?
- I'm feeling emotional.

01:22:47.880 --> 01:22:49.459
What's that?

01:22:50.803 --> 01:22:54.555
- It's where I keep my Kleenex.
- He's very depressed, Neville.

01:22:54.655 --> 01:22:57.459
Isn't it wonderful to see a man
get in touch with his feelings?

01:22:57.559 --> 01:22:59.793
- There's something going on here.
- Oh, I hope so.

01:22:59.893 --> 01:23:03.828
Excuse me, gentlemen.
I need to be alone.

01:23:03.928 --> 01:23:07.669
Feeling a bit suicidal.

01:23:07.769 --> 01:23:12.021
What?
This isn't like Rod!

01:23:13.394 --> 01:23:15.610
Hey! He's in the shed!

01:23:15.710 --> 01:23:18.529
- What?
- He's in the shed!

01:23:20.267 --> 01:23:22.348
Gentlemen, I admit it.

01:23:22.448 --> 01:23:25.985
I behaved disgracefully
to my son in the past.

01:23:26.085 --> 01:23:28.424
I don't know if I can
live with myself.

01:23:28.524 --> 01:23:31.863
So, going to the shed.

01:23:31.963 --> 01:23:34.928
Mother always said that when
you're naughty, you go to the shed.

01:23:35.028 --> 01:23:36.712
And I've been naughty.

01:23:38.654 --> 01:23:40.588
God, I'm depressed!

01:23:49.999 --> 01:23:51.296
Going to the shed.

01:23:55.306 --> 01:23:57.397
- It's going well. Where's the body?
- Over there.

01:23:58.808 --> 01:24:02.210
Come on, come on! Give it here.
Let's go! We gotta go!

01:24:04.415 --> 01:24:06.063
What is going on?

01:24:06.163 --> 01:24:09.501
- He and Vince did get very upset.
- It was so touching.

01:24:09.601 --> 01:24:13.737
Oh, God. I've undervalued
Vince's talent all these years.

01:24:13.837 --> 01:24:17.407
And his extraordinary charm.
Let's not forget that.

01:24:17.507 --> 01:24:20.746
What a dear boy he was,
my Vince, and still is.

01:24:20.846 --> 01:24:25.151
Good-looking young lad.
Christ, he's attractive.

01:24:25.251 --> 01:24:27.418
- Such style!
- Where is Vince?

01:24:27.518 --> 01:24:30.987
- That's a good question.
- Vince?

01:24:31.087 --> 01:24:34.861
I never went to one of my
birthday parties, the bastard!

01:24:34.961 --> 01:24:38.597
- His! His!
- His birthday parties, the bastard!

01:24:38.697 --> 01:24:43.303
I'm the bastard! I'm such a bastard
I can't stand it anymore!

01:24:43.403 --> 01:24:47.311
I can't face it! Oh, the shame!
I feel terrible!

01:24:47.411 --> 01:24:51.011
I don't know what I'm gonna do,
but I've got a pretty shrewd idea...

01:24:51.111 --> 01:24:53.347
it's not gonna be very nice!

01:24:53.447 --> 01:24:56.218
- I'm taking the wuss's way out!
- Is he all right?

01:24:56.318 --> 01:24:58.919
He's probably in one
of his black moods.

01:24:59.019 --> 01:25:00.789
What black moods?

01:25:00.889 --> 01:25:06.230
End of the road! I can't take it
any longer! I'm going to finish it now!

01:25:06.330 --> 01:25:07.730
My God!

01:25:09.064 --> 01:25:11.468
- Has he got a gun?
- Gun? What gun?

01:25:11.568 --> 01:25:13.701
Where's the gun?
The gun!

01:25:13.801 --> 01:25:14.801
What?

01:25:16.458 --> 01:25:20.075
I'm at the end of the road!
I'm very near the end.

01:25:20.175 --> 01:25:22.676
I'm gonna...
I can see the end of the road.

01:25:22.776 --> 01:25:25.881
I'm makin' up my mind.
It's not an easy...

01:25:25.981 --> 01:25:28.651
He's forgiven you.
Be sensible!

01:25:28.751 --> 01:25:31.922
At least it looks like
the end of the road.

01:25:32.022 --> 01:25:34.171
Now I'm thinkin' about it.

01:25:37.815 --> 01:25:39.282
I'll make my mind up
any moment now.

01:25:50.027 --> 01:25:54.123
I love you, kid.
Forgive me.

01:26:17.858 --> 01:26:19.972
Hurry! Hurry!

01:26:20.072 --> 01:26:22.757
One! Two! Come on!

01:26:26.567 --> 01:26:29.648
- Oh, no!
- Don't look!

01:26:29.748 --> 01:26:32.657
- Why were your men so slow?
- Sorry, we didn't realize...

01:26:32.757 --> 01:26:34.754
- This isn't Rod McCain.
- What?

01:26:34.854 --> 01:26:39.425
I spent 15 years working at Octopus,
and this isn't Rod McCa...

01:26:39.525 --> 01:26:41.431
I was in the garden
when I heard a gunshot...

01:26:41.531 --> 01:26:44.232
- Father!
- I'm afraid he's dead.

01:26:44.332 --> 01:26:45.581
- No!
- Yes.

01:26:47.956 --> 01:26:50.571
- What are you doing?
- He shot himself.

01:26:50.671 --> 01:26:52.271
No! Why?

01:26:52.710 --> 01:26:55.242
He wasn't in one of his
black moods, was he?

01:26:55.342 --> 01:26:58.080
He just couldn't live
with what he'd done to you.

01:26:58.180 --> 01:27:00.215
- But I'd forgiven him.
- I know.

01:27:00.315 --> 01:27:03.915
Oh, Dad! Dad! Dad!

01:27:05.175 --> 01:27:06.457
- Vince.
- What?

01:27:06.557 --> 01:27:08.461
- There's something you should know.
- What?

01:27:08.561 --> 01:27:11.207
He left Octopus to you.

01:27:13.383 --> 01:27:16.410
So he did love me after all!

01:27:25.797 --> 01:27:27.889
You're fired.

01:27:57.330 --> 01:28:00.216
Rollo, there's something
I need to ask you.

01:28:00.316 --> 01:28:02.551
It's about sex.

01:28:02.651 --> 01:28:03.651
What?

